  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>Medical information and emergency contacts are crucial for Masters Rugby League players. While we don't have separate dedicated fields for this information, you can include comprehensive medical details in the player's notes field during registration.</p>

  <h3>Recording Medical Information</h3>
  <p>Use the "Notes" field when adding or editing a player to record important medical information:</p>

  <h4>Essential Medical Information to Record</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Allergies</strong> — List all known allergies (e.g., "Allergic to penicillin, bee stings")</li>
    <li><strong>Medications</strong> — Current medications and dosages (e.g., "Blood pressure medication: 10mg daily")</li>
    <li><strong>Medical Conditions</strong> — Chronic conditions (e.g., "Asthma, requires inhaler")</li>
    <li><strong>Previous Injuries</strong> — Significant past injuries (e.g., "ACL reconstruction 2018, full recovery")</li>
    <li><strong>Emergency Contacts</strong> — Alternative contacts if player cannot be reached</li>
    <li><strong>Blood Type</strong> — If known (e.g., "Blood type: O+")</li>
    <li><strong>Medical Alerts</strong> — Any special considerations (e.g., "Diabetic, carries glucose monitor")</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Emergency Contact Format</h4>
  <p>Use a consistent format for emergency contacts in the notes:</p>
  <div class="alert alert-info">
    <strong>Example:</strong><br>
    <code>EMERGENCY CONTACT: John Smith (Husband) - 0412 345 678<br>
    MEDICAL: Asthma - inhaler required, allergic to nuts<br>
    MEDICATION: Lisinopril 10mg daily for blood pressure</code>
  </div>

  <h3>Best Practices for Medical Information</h3>

  <h4>Organization</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Use Clear Labels</strong> — Start each section with clear labels (EMERGENCY, MEDICAL, MEDICATION, ALLERGIES)</li>
    <li><strong>Be Specific</strong> — Include dosages, frequencies, and specific details</li>
    <li><strong>Keep Updated</strong> — Review and update medical information regularly</li>
    <li><strong>Privacy Considerations</strong> — Only include information necessary for emergency response</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Emergency Response Information</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Primary Contact</strong> — Player's emergency contact details</li>
    <li><strong>Alternative Contact</strong> — Secondary contact if primary is unavailable</li>
    <li><strong>Relationship</strong> — Specify relationship to player (spouse, child, friend)</li>
    <li><strong>Contact Preference</strong> — Preferred method (phone, text, email)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Medical Conditions Common in Masters Rugby</h3>

  <h4>Cardiovascular</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>High blood pressure (hypertension)</li>
    <li>Heart conditions or previous cardiac events</li>
    <li>Medications for cholesterol or heart health</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Respiratory</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Asthma or exercise-induced bronchospasm</li>
    <li>COPD or other lung conditions</li>
    <li>Allergies affecting breathing</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Musculoskeletal</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Previous joint injuries or surgeries</li>
    <li>Arthritis or joint degeneration</li>
    <li>Chronic back or neck issues</li>
    <li>Previous fractures or breaks</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Other Common Conditions</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Diabetes (Type 1 or 2)</li>
    <li>Epilepsy or seizure disorders</li>
    <li>Migraine headaches</li>
    <li>Mental health considerations</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Emergency Contact Guidelines</h3>

  <h4>Who to List</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Spouse or Partner</strong> — Most common emergency contact</li>
    <li><strong>Adult Children</strong> — For players whose children are available</li>
    <li><strong>Close Friends</strong> — Reliable friends who know the player well</li>
    <li><strong>Medical Proxy</strong> — Designated person for medical decisions</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Contact Information to Include</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Full Name</strong> — Complete name of emergency contact</li>
    <li><strong>Relationship</strong> — How they are related to the player</li>
    <li><strong>Phone Numbers</strong> — Mobile and landline if available</li>
    <li><strong>Alternative Contact</strong> — Backup contact if primary is unreachable</li>
    <li><strong>Availability</strong> — When the contact is typically available</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Updating Medical Information</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Navigate to your club's player list</li>
    <li>Find the player whose information needs updating</li>
    <li>Click the "Edit" button next to their name</li>
    <li>Scroll to the "Notes" section</li>
    <li>Update the medical information using the established format</li>
    <li>Save the changes</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Privacy and Confidentiality</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Access Control</strong> — Medical information is only visible to club delegates and administrators</li>
    <li><strong>Emergency Access</strong> — Information may be shared with medical personnel in emergencies</li>
    <li><strong>Data Protection</strong> — All medical information is stored securely and encrypted</li>
    <li><strong>Player Consent</strong> — Players should be informed about how their medical information will be used</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Recommended Medical Information Template</h3>
  <div class="alert alert-success">
    <strong>Use this template in the Notes field:</strong>
    <pre><code>EMERGENCY CONTACT: [Name] ([Relationship]) - [Phone Number]
ALTERNATIVE CONTACT: [Name] ([Relationship]) - [Phone Number]
MEDICAL CONDITIONS: [List any chronic conditions]
ALLERGIES: [List all known allergies]
MEDICATIONS: [Current medications with dosages]
PREVIOUS INJURIES: [Significant past injuries]
OTHER NOTES: [Additional relevant information]</code></pre>
  </div>

